You look up at the vases on the shelf, well they are pretty why did you want to look at them? Oh, wait you mean the one that looks like a key? It seems like a good possibility that it could be in there. Unless it's the key vase that has a bunch of padlocks. To be honest you never remembered taking a key-shaped vase. Never the less you're going to need to break it in order to get it's key, but how would one break it?

Hmm...

>Grab piggy log, and look cool doing it

> Piggy log
>Grab piggy log, and look cool doing it

You grab your piggy log from the pile of logs underneath the shelf, and grip it fiercely but not too fiercely because of its fragile aspects. You take a step back and take aim. You shut your eyes and let your strength shroud you. Before you throw the log you say in a whisper "You're about to make the pot go... Timber. With all your might you throw the hefty log and...

...You miss Terribly! You look up in anticipation to see if the log has been decimated, but seems completely unaffected by your pun! Maybe you must make a better pun to break the pot.

>Grab your piggy log again

> Grab your piggy log again
>Grab your piggy log again

You walk over to your piggy log and realize that you've broken it! Aw great, it was one of it's kind too. You lift up the log knowing what a childish thing you've done and realize that a key came out of the ginormous hole in the bottom.

You slap your face in shame, how did you forget that you left the key IN THAT LOG? Like that's the only use of that log, there's nothing special about that log beside guarding that key with its life (assuming it had one). Well, might as well forget that this dilemma ever happened and go down and get that flint and steel.

>Go down into the basement

> Go down
>Go down into the basement

You fling open the basement door and head down cautiously. The sound of hissing and rattling can be heard in the darkness below. You carefully walk down and take in some of the dry air, that hasn't been breathed in for about 2 months. The cold stone on the floor makes the hairs on your body tingle a little (even though you don't visibly have any hairs). Before you can feel anymore weird about being down here you should just go and get the flint and steel.

>Grab the lamp on top of the crafting bench

> Grab the lamp on the crafting bench
>Grab the lamp on top of the crafting bench

You walk slowly drag your feet over to the crafting bench on the other side of the room. The lamp containing the flint and steel sit there covered in dust, from its lack of use. You feel heavy breathing on your neck, but nothing seems to be around you. You can tell somethings living down here. You quickly grab the lamp and equip it because it's your old fighting weapon! You hear a loud thump! from behind you, but you're too afraid to look behind you... However, you can tell a brawl is about to begin.

