Alright since your hysteria is finally lowered you can try to figure out how your gonna deal with this scoundrel in your basement. Maybe you can contact the toughest guy you know Ace Quarter. Well since there's no magical device that allows you to contact people through the touch of a button, so you're gonna have to do it the OLD FASHION WAY which would be getting one of your carrier chickens to send a letter to him. Pfft, saying it aloud makes it sound like making popped corn! Hopefully you can get this done quick. Well before you can even attempt to go outside it's pretty dark, you should light your lamp.

>Light your lamp

> Lamp
>Light your lamp

After scratching the rocks together you eventually create a spark, which lights the candle. Great! Now you are able to defend yourself against any danger that tries to attack you, or against tree's that block your way, man you feel safer already.

>Go outside

> Outside
>Go outside

You exit your cramped home, and the outside world greets you with a gust of wind, it's super refreshing and relaxing. Ironic cause of the situation your in currently. Well, you'd obviously remember that your chicken coop is right next to your house cause you obviously didn't want it to be too far away cause people might kill them! Maybe you should install a door to the coop in your house.

>Walk over to the chicken coop

> Coop
>Walk over to the chicken coop

You walk over to the front of the coop, the air here feels a little strange. Maybe it's because of all the stress you're going through? Soon enough you begin to hear loud thuds and a shadowy figure stands behind the coop, you bring your lamp closer to see what the huge figure may be.

Oh... It's a soleclops...

>Enter coop

> Enter coop
>Enter coop

To make your day better this soleclops has to come and pester your chickens? That's pretty sad, and frustrating at the same time. Well, luckily this one doesn't seem to be as big as other ones you've seen before (trust me they can get HUMONGOUS). Just ignore it, for now, it doesn't seem to be doing any harm besides eyeballing you.

The smell of the coop every time you enter always bothered you, but not today. You see your two chickens Benley and Newtford here just doing nothing... Wait there's supposed to be three chickens. Where's Frotyke?

>Greet Newtford

> Greetings
>Greet Newtford

You bend down and rub Newtford's head, man he's such a good chicken especially for his young age. You look around for Benley only to notice that he's at the other side of the coop pecking at water droplets... sigh. Benley, Benley, Benley. The worst of all the chickens, he's has no loyalty towards anyone. You've taken him to multiple institutes to find out what's his deal but they all say the same thing "Seems like a fine chicken to me." For some reason with you, he doesn't seem to give a DAMN you exist. He doesn't even seem to want to spend time with either Newtford or Frotyke. That's Benley for you... Same old, same old.

>Write your distress letter to quarter

> Letter
>Write your distress letter to quarter

You go over to your little desk at the northern side of the coop and write a distress letter about that scoundrel that's in your basement, and you also talk about how you've been doing lately cause it's been a while since you guys talked, you call over your partner in crime Newtford and tie the letter with a ribbon around his body and he scurries off as fast as possible. While you watch Newtford run off you begin to hear thuds, and see the Soleclops chase Newtford as if it was a snack. Due to the soleclops massive size he eventually catches up with Newtford and grabs him as if he was an inanimate object. By surprise the soleclops stuffs the helpless chicken into his mouth and swallow him WHOLE.
It was a brutal sight to see.

WHYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYY!!!

